# AEGIS DECISION LOG

## 2026-01-26
- Project initiated under the name "Aegis"
- Defined as an OS-native Intent Engine, not a chatbot or agent
- Adopted First Law: consequences before action
- Chose illumination over automation as core philosophy
- Established Intent Card as the primary interface primitive
- Explicitly rejected silent autonomy in v1

## 2026-02-03
Decision: Formalize Aegis as a public, version-controlled repository.
Rationale: Canonical governance, architecture, and security documents reached sufficient maturity
to require durable versioning, external review, and change tracking.
Impact: All future changes are governed by AEGIS_META_INDEX.md and logged explicitly.

## 2026-03-23
Decision: Archive this repository and migrate to aegis-initiative/aegis-origin.
Rationale: The AEGIS project has matured into a multi-repository ecosystem under the
aegis-initiative GitHub organization. This repository — the original V0 — served as
the monolithic origin from which all current repos were decomposed. Its contents have
evolved into aegis-constitution (governance charter), aegis-governance (protocol specs),
aegis-core (enforcement engine), aegis (governance hub), aegis-platform (operator dashboard),
and aegis-sdk (client libraries).
Impact: This repository is frozen as a historical artifact. No further development will
occur here. The DOI snapshot preserves the V0 state for provenance and citation.
